description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BANK Health Care Support Workers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are expanding our workforce which brings incredible opportunities for YOU to join our nurse bank. The variety of areas you could work in will add to your experience and contribute to your personal development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please take a look at the attached ‘additional information’ to explore our ward areas so you can see which area excites you the most. By joining our teams you will be able to work flexibly choosing your own hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust provides support for all staff working on theHCSW bank. You will be invited to attend a full Trust induction which includes mandatory training. We arrange a study day and a shadow shift where you will be supernumerary in order to achieve a set of competencies to support you in practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This opportunity is based at Royal Papworth Hospital Cambridge Biomedical Campus, our beautiful new hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What our patients say…..&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;“During the operation all of the doctors and nurses assured me of the safe process which was completed as planned. Excellent 5 star job done”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;“The facilities at Royal Papworth are superb - a wonderful hospital. The staff - all staff, make Royal Papworth a top class experience”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;“Staff were friendly, welcoming, helpful and professional. I felt relaxed and at ease during my visit because of the superb way I was treated by all staff - A credit to Royal Papworth and the NHS”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular shortlisting takes place and if you are shortlisted you will be contacted for a Skype interview.&lt;/p&gt;
